      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>LEAD: Blue Velvet  Written and directed by David Lynch. With Kyle Maclachlan, Isabella Rossellini, Dennis Hopper, Laura Dern. 1986. Lorimar Home Video.  120 minutes. $79.95.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>LEAD: Blue Velvet  Written and directed by David Lynch. With Kyle Maclachlan, Isabella Rossellini, Dennis Hopper, Laura Dern. 1986. Lorimar Home Video.  120 minutes. $79.95.</p>
        <p>Blue Velvet  Written and directed by David Lynch. With Kyle Maclachlan, Isabella Rossellini, Dennis Hopper, Laura Dern. 1986. Lorimar Home Video.  120 minutes. $79.95.</p>
        <p>What's it like to watch this bombshell at home? It's not easy. Shock value has contributed greatly to this film's reputation, as has David Lynch's genuinely perverse and original vision. But the effect is more crude and disturbing on the small screen than it was in the theater, and if viewing is interrupted, the damage is even greater; ''Blue Velvet'' must be seen as a whole if it's to be seen at all.</p>
        <p>Mr. Lynch's startling effects are undiminished, as in the film's unforgettable opening. But much of ''Blue Velvet'' takes place in a darkened room that becomes so murky here that the actors can barely be seen. And Dennis Hopper's bold, frightening performance as a fetishistic sadist begins, in this different context, to border on the absurd.</p>
      </block>
